The article is a memorandum from President Barack Obama, dated January 14, 2011. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to establish the Richard C. Holbrooke Award for Diplomacy in honor of Richard C. Holbrooke, a renowned diplomat. The award is meant to recognize distinguished Americans who have made significant contributions to diplomacy. The Secretary of State is instructed to present a list of nominees to the President, from which up to five individuals or groups will be selected to receive the award. The memorandum also grants authority to publish the memorandum in the Federal Register.